&lt;/ul&gt;</content><category term="k8s"></category><category term="k8s"></category></entry><entry><title>Kubernetes Architecture</title><link href="/kubernetes-architecture.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2022-05-21T21:36:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-07-10T17:09:00+00:00</updated><author><name>Hephzibah Pon Cellat Arulprakash</name></author><id>tag:None,2022-05-21:/kubernetes-architecture.html</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;A kubernetes cluster is made up of one or more control plane and worker nodes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Control Plane&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Components of control plane are,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kube-apiserver&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;etcd&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;controller manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kube-scheduler&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Worker Nodes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Components of a worker node are,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kubelet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kube proxy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;container runtime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><category term="k8s"></category><category term="k8s"></category></entry></feed>